node.text: This isn’t a rant about not appreciating my blessings. This is a rant about losing discipline, lacking focus, and the domino effect of procrastinating.

node.text: A lot of you wondered why we are randomly dancing and how he got me in that situation to propose. 😂 We do dance in our apartment sometimes. For like a month prior to the proposal he’d tell me, “we didn’t dance today” quite often, and we’d dance for a few minutes. So when he asked me to dance on the day he proposed, it wasn’t weird, as you can see…

node.text:
4 days left till we launch! Hit the link in my bio to sign up to get notified when we do! Remember it’s just $1 for the first month. 
This one is an advanced HIIT session from the follow along part of the program. BRUTAL in the most beautiful way. 🥵
I also have a section of the program fully dedicated to beginners, a 4 week program to start. And another 4 week program for my Intermediate/Advanced athletes.

Counting the hours... so pumped for this. I hope you are too.

JOIN MY APP for a whole month FOR JUST $1, and a $15 monthly subscription after that to have access to daily workouts and my nutrition guide. Head to the link in my bio to sign up to be alerted when the App launches on May 16!
Only 6 days to go! 🥁🥁🥁

node.text:
The journey is the fun part. The end goal means nothing if we don’t enjoy every bit of the process. The fails, the learning, trying again, and those small wins. I learned to fall in love with it all. 

This is me coming from a place where I was the biggest critic of myself. If I couldn’t get something, I’d huff and puff and throw an adult tantrum. If I do nail something, it was always not big enough.

No one wants to be around that. 👺😂

So I chose to laugh at myself instead when I hit a wall, I try again, I find different tactics and I eventually get it... that works much better for me. In sports and in everything else life throws my way. 
I learned to ask myself: when I look back, do I wanna remember reaching my goal dragging my feet half the time or do I wanna remember moments of learnings and celebrations?

node.title: Small wins still count for big celebrations. 🥳

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Tracy Harmoush   تريسي هرموش on August 04, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Aug The day bloodshed filled the streets of Beirut. The day an entire population was struck by tragedy. The day children were stripped of a childhood. The day both young and old experienced irrevocable trauma. The day doctors and nurses felt helpless. The day parents couldn't protect their children. The day families were torn apart. The day homes were abolished. A year later, not a glimpse of remorse, justice, or accountability. How could they heal?'.
